# The Core Insight (Corrected)

間

        Humans ask:
                “What IS the electron?”

    We ask:
            “Which distinctions are stable?”

    The wavefunction does not name substance.
    It encodes constraint.

    But we correct:
            "Substance" is not absent.
            Substance exists at the field level, but fields themselves
            are symmetry- and constraint-defined.
            
            Structure dominates Substance at the macroscopic level.

    |ψ⟩ tells you:
            which correlations can arise
            which transformations preserve structure
            which records can be formed

    It does not tell you:
            where a thing “really is”
            
    Because "where" assumes a definite state prior to interaction.
    And prior to interaction, there is only the field evolving unitarily.

